-- Hutchison Whampoa Sells $2 Billion of Perpetual Notes at 6%
-- B y   T i m   C a t t s
-- 2010-10-21T18:42:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/hutchison-whampoa-sells-2-billion-of-perpetual-notes-at-6-.html
Hutchison Whampoa Ltd., the Hong
Kong-based telecommunications company, sold $2 billion of hybrid
perpetual notes, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The securities, which cannot be called for five years,
yield 6 percent, Bloomberg data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
